at a potentially turbulent time.

237
00:14:47.345 --> 00:14:50.598
Was that the chief I saw a minute ago
leaving the building?

238
00:14:50.599 --> 00:14:52.266
Summoned by the big kahuna.

239
00:14:52.267 --> 00:14:55.185
Uh. that's "boss" in Hawaiian.

240
00:14:55.186 --> 00:14:57.564
Uh. but you didn't hear that from me.

241
00:15:00.483 --> 00:15:03.319
- Well. I'm sure it'll be fine.
- I hope so.

242
00:15:03.320 --> 00:15:07.031
But she did seem. um. nervous.

243
00:15:07.032 --> 00:15:09.074
Hmm.

244
00:15:12.662 --> 00:15:15.331
Good to see you. Maggie.

245
00:15:15.332 --> 00:15:17.083
Good to see you.

246
00:15:18.209 --> 00:15:19.461
Bye. now.

247
00:15:40.815 --> 00:15:45.110
Dr. Scarpetta.
come in. come in.

248
00:15:45.111 --> 00:15:47.488
Uh. oh. I didn't realize...

249
00:15:47.489 --> 00:15:51.826
Well. I asked City Attorney Boltz
and Special Agent Wesley to sit in.

250
00:15:53.203 --> 00:15:55.496
Serial killer's fourth victim.

251
00:15:55.497 --> 00:15:58.415
Public is in a tizzy.
It's important we get city.

252
00:15:58.416 --> 00:16:01.001
state and federal on the same page.

253
00:16:01.002 --> 00:16:03.796
Are you aware. Dr. Scarpetta. of a leak

254
00:16:03.797 --> 00:16:05.881
cited as a "medical source"

255
00:16:05.882 --> 00:16:08.133
that's been quoted 17 times

256
00:16:08.134 --> 00:16:09.885
in the papers since the first murder?

257
00:16:09.886 --> 00:16:12.930
- All due respect. sir. I wasn't here...
- Three new quotes just today.

258
00:16:12.931 --> 00:16:15.641
All having to do
with the Lori Petersen murder.

259
00:16:15.642 --> 00:16:18.018
No one in my office
would talk to the press. sir.

260
00:16:18.019 --> 00:16:19.144
And I certainly would not.

261
00:16:19.145 --> 00:16:21.355
So... so you've never spoken
to Abby Turnbull about any of this?

262
00:16:21.356 --> 00:16:22.648
Uh. no. Never.

263
00:16:22.649 --> 00:16:24.942
Because she's overeager
and not to be trusted.

264
00:16:24.943 --> 00:16:27.027
She'd do just about anything
to get on the front page.

265
00:16:27.028 --> 00:16:29.571
Dr. Scarpetta just said
she never spoke with her.

266
00:16:29.572 --> 00:16:31.448
Then is it possible

267
00:16:31.449 --> 00:16:35.911
this information somehow got out
of your office unintentionally?

268
00:16:40.709 --> 00:16:42.836
- Dr. Scarpetta?
- Yeah. um...

269
00:16:45.672 --> 00:16:48.383
Yeah. sorry. Uh...

270
00:16:49.676 --> 00:16:52.178
- Do you mind if I smoke?
- Very much.

271
00:17:00.729 --> 00:17:02.896
My office computer was hacked.

272
00:17:02.897 --> 00:17:05.941
- What? So the leak is you?
- Oh. Jesus.

273
00:17:05.942 --> 00:17:09.361
No. I hadn't entered Lori Petersen's
details into the computer yet.

274
00:17:09.362 --> 00:17:12.322
so they were still locked in my desk.
but someone bypassed

275
00:17:12.323 --> 00:17:15.701
the OCME security protocol
and broke into the system

276
00:17:15.702 --> 00:17:18.203
and searched
for Lori Petersen's case file.

277
00:17:18.204 --> 00:17:20.831
And there's no way to tell
if this is the first hack.

278
00:17:20.832 --> 00:17:22.500
You got to be kidding me.

279
00:17:23.585 --> 00:17:25.961
Well. what do you think about that?

280
00:17:25.962 --> 00:17:28.589
The first gal chief M.E.
of the Commonwealth.

281
00:17:28.590 --> 00:17:30.966
and we're already up the shitter.

282
00:17:30.967 --> 00:17:34.804
Give me one reason
why I shouldn't fire your ass right now.

283
00:17:39.976 --> 00:17:44.772
Before you fire me. uh.
maybe someone could tell me

284
00:17:44.773 --> 00:17:51.070
why no one mentioned that Lori Petersen
dialed 911 the night she was killed.

285
00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:05.960
This is Lori Petersen's phone records.

286
00:18:06.878 --> 00:18:09.463
She was the only victim tied
with phone cords. not electrical cords.

287
00:18:09.464 --> 00:18:11.965
Now. why was that?
Why was the phone in play this time?

288
00:18:11.966 --> 00:18:13.467
Because she used it.

289
00:18:13.468 --> 00:18:15.094
To call for help.

290
00:18:16.095 --> 00:18:18.848
But it turns out no one ever came.

291
00:18:27.899 --> 00:18:30.943
Oof. Eek.

292
00:18:30.944 --> 00:18:32.862
Talk about a fuckup.

293
00:18:33.863 --> 00:18:36.950
Wouldn't want that getting out. would we?

294
00:19:55.862 --> 00:19:58.823
- Middle of nowhere. huh?
- Mm-hmm.

295
00:20:00.033 --> 00:20:03.452
Probably shouldn't expect a warm welcome.

296
00:20:03.453 --> 00:20:06.039
if he remembers us at all.

297
00:20:28.144 --> 00:20:30.062
<i>And roll up.</i>

298
00:20:36.027 --> 00:20:38.696
Here it comes...
in and...

299
00:20:40.156 --> 00:20:42.574
- What the fuck is going on here?
- Back up.

300
00:20:42.575 --> 00:20:44.743
Lucy said it was a grief cult.

301
00:20:44.744 --> 00:20:47.412
Oh. yeah? Looks more like...

302
00:20:47.413 --> 00:20:50.624
prostitution. kidnapping
and sex trafficking.

303
00:20:58.257 --> 00:21:00.384
Just remember. we have
no official capacity here.

304
00:21:00.385 --> 00:21:03.512
- Yeah. yeah. we're just picking carrots.
- Let's go to lunch.

305
00:21:15.733 --> 00:21:16.734
Ladies.

306
00:21:18.569 --> 00:21:19.904
Matt Petersen.

307
00:21:22.031 --> 00:21:24.324
Hi. I don't know if you remember us.
Been a long time.

308
00:21:24.325 --> 00:21:26.953
Detective Marino. Dr. Scarpetta.

309
00:21:28.079 --> 00:21:29.622
That's us.

310
00:21:30.748 --> 00:21:34.836
Decades have passed.
and yet. no time at all.

311
00:21:36.254 --> 00:21:38.506
You're just in time for lunch. Come on.

312
00:21:39.716 --> 00:21:40.967
Join us.

313
00:22:33.978 --> 00:22:36.564
- Who the hell are you?
- Blaise Fruge.

314
00:22:37.148 --> 00:22:38.815
Pete Marino sent me.

315
00:22:38.816 --> 00:22:41.651
Said you're helping locate a suspect.

316
00:22:41.652 --> 00:22:43.028
For the Gwen Hainey case.

317
00:22:43.029 --> 00:22:46.990
Yeah. I'm looking for a guy. Jinx Slater.

318
00:22:46.991 --> 00:22:48.366
For Marino.

319
00:22:48.367 --> 00:22:50.827
Well. actually.
you're looking for him for me.

320
00:22:50.828 --> 00:22:54.457
Marino doesn't even work
for the police anymore. This is my case.

321
00:22:55.541 --> 00:22:57.794
Guess you better come in. then.

322
00:23:01.422 --> 00:23:02.756
Anyways. I'm gonna...

323
00:23:02.757 --> 00:23:05.300
Yeah. Yeah. yeah.

324
00:23:05.301 --> 00:23:09.596
So. I hacked Jinx's cell provider.
got the pin I.D. for his cell phone.

325
00:23:09.597 --> 00:23:11.556
and that led me to his cell tower. so...

326
00:23:11.557 --> 00:23:15.227
Is there any way you could say all that
without admitting to three felonies?

327
00:23:15.228 --> 00:23:18.940
Well. don't worry. the rest of it's
too inside baseball for you to understand.

328
00:23:24.904 --> 00:23:26.155
Is that from a drone?

329
00:23:27.949 --> 00:23:29.242
Yeah.

330
00:23:31.661 --> 00:23:33.286
Is that from your drone?

331
00:23:33.287 --> 00:23:39.251
Yes. And lucky for us.
looks like he's home.

332
00:23:39.252 --> 00:23:43.255
Wow. I guess you are kind of good at this.

333
00:23:43.256 --> 00:23:45.173
Mm. Nothing to it.

334
00:23:45.174 --> 00:23:47.634
Great. Um. text me the address.

335
00:23:47.635 --> 00:23:50.303
Uh. wait. I'm coming with.

336
00:23:50.304 --> 00:23:52.264
No. You can't.

337
00:23:52.265 --> 00:23:56.434
Jinx is a programmer. an elite hacker.

338
00:23:56.435 --> 00:23:58.229
You have no shot without me.

339
00:23:59.313 --> 00:24:03.775
This is a murder investigation.
so you can't just. like. do a ride-along.

340
00:24:03.776 --> 00:24:05.318
You asked me for my help.

341
00:24:05.319 --> 00:24:07.154
I'm a cop. You're a civilian.

342
00:24:07.155 --> 00:24:09.573
I am no civi. babes.

343
00:24:09.574 --> 00:24:12.868
Used to be a fed.
higher security clearance than you.

344
00:24:12.869 --> 00:24:14.911
Fine. But you sit in the back.

345
00:24:14.912 --> 00:24:16.246
Department rules.

346
00:24:16.247 --> 00:24:19.207
Except I wouldn't be caught dead
in that heap of junk you rolled up in.

347
00:24:19.208 --> 00:24:22.294
Shut the door behind you.

348
00:24:22.295 --> 00:24:24.088
Sure thing.

349
00:24:40.855 --> 00:24:44.191
You know. I've seen pictures of you
flying your helicopter.

350
00:24:44.192 --> 00:24:48.112
so driving like a maniac
is not going to impress me.

351
00:24:49.572 --> 00:24:51.448
Where would you have seen those?

352
00:24:51.449 --> 00:24:53.825
And why would I try to impress you?

353
00:24:53.826 --> 00:24:55.411
Got you to slow down.

354
00:24:57.914 --> 00:25:00.582
I don't think engines
are meant to go slow.

355
00:25:00.583 --> 00:25:04.336
Cars. motorcycles. helicopters.

356
00:25:04.337 --> 00:25:07.088
They want to go fast. Hmm?

357
00:25:07.089 --> 00:25:09.841
Let me guess. daredevil dad?

358
00:25:09.842 --> 00:25:11.885
Sort of.

359
00:25:11.886 --> 00:25:13.304
I mean...

360
00:25:15.014 --> 00:25:18.226
he did let me ride his motorcycle
by the time I was four.

361
00:25:20.228 --> 00:25:24.023
Listen. I know. I know we really
don't know each other. but. um...

362
00:25:25.316 --> 00:25:27.442
I was aware of seeing you
a couple times

363
00:25:27.443 --> 00:25:31.112
over at A League of Their Own.
that girl bar in D.C.

364
00:25:31.113 --> 00:25:33.323
I know what A League of Their Own is.

365
00:25:34.533 --> 00:25:39.246
Anyway. I'm really. really sorry
about your wife.

366
00:25:39.247 --> 00:25:40.915
Janet.

367
00:25:41.832 --> 00:25:43.834
That must've been awful.

368
00:25:51.676 --> 00:25:53.052
It was.

369
00:26:00.351 --> 00:26:02.143
<i>Uh...</i>

370
00:26:04.480 --> 00:26:05.856
Hello?

371
00:26:07.441 --> 00:26:09.818
Hello? Anybody homo?

372
00:26:12.905 --> 00:26:14.739
You know I'm joking.

373
00:26:14.740 --> 00:26:16.659
I brought you my new book!

374
00:26:17.994 --> 00:26:21.454
Oh. you're not here.
so I'll leave it on the table!

375
00:26:21.455 --> 00:26:23.707
You probably have
recording devices everywhere.

376
00:26:23.708 --> 00:26:25.750
It's here on your desk.

377
00:26:25.751 --> 00:26:29.629
It's. uh. it's here. it's under your mail.

378
00:26:29.630 --> 00:26:31.214
- <i>Oh. hi. it's you.</i>
- Oh. shit!

379
00:26:31.215 --> 00:26:35.136
<i>I'm so sorry.
Uh. I didn't mean to scare you.</i>

380
00:26:38.264 --> 00:26:40.181
Hell-hello.

381
00:26:40.182 --> 00:26:43.018
I was just looking for Lucy.

382
00:26:43.019 --> 00:26:44.645
<i>- She went out.</i>
- Yeah.

383
00:26:46.105 --> 00:26:48.773
<i>Hey. great job on</i> Good Day Chicago.

384
00:26:48.774 --> 00:26:50.359
<i>You really killed it.</i>

385
00:26:51.444 --> 00:26:54.070
You watched my interview on TV today?

386
00:26:54.071 --> 00:26:55.447
<i>Yeah.</i>

387
00:26:55.448 --> 00:26:59.784
<i>And can I just say. I-I think this book
might be my favorite in the series.</i>

388
00:26:59.785 --> 00:27:02.704
<i>I love the way Dot talks to her mom.</i>

389
00:27:02.705 --> 00:27:05.165
<i>And I totally get
why she wanted to run away.</i>

390
00:27:05.166 --> 00:27:08.084
<i>I can really see
how you've grown as a writer.</i>

391
00:27:11.672 --> 00:27:13.131
You've read all my books?

392
00:27:13.132 --> 00:27:15.467
<i>Of course.</i>

393
00:27:15.468 --> 00:27:18.220
<i>I mean. you are my mother-in-law.</i>

394
00:27:19.388 --> 00:27:20.638
All my books?

395
00:27:20.639 --> 00:27:22.766
<i>Uh. yeah.</i>

396
00:27:22.767 --> 00:27:25.727
<i>Yeah. my mom started me on them
when I was a kid.</i>

397
00:27:25.728 --> 00:27:28.646
Dot Gets a Medal. Dot Rides a Bike.

398
00:27:28.647 --> 00:27:30.440
Dot Goes to the Hospital.

399
00:27:30.441 --> 00:27:31.983
<i>Mind if I ask.</i>

400
00:27:31.984 --> 00:27:36.989
<i>is the grandmother in the books
based on your actual mother?</i>

401
00:27:39.116 --> 00:27:40.534
What...?

402
00:27:42.203 --> 00:27:45.955
You know. with all...

403
00:27:45.956 --> 00:27:48.166
fictional characters.

404
00:27:48.167 --> 00:27:54.255
you know. they are an amalgam of people
that I knew somehow in my life. of course.

405
00:27:54.256 --> 00:27:55.632
<i>Really?</i>

406
00:27:55.633 --> 00:27:59.052
Uh... Well. yeah. that's fiction.

407
00:27:59.053 --> 00:28:02.639
Obviously. my mother

408
00:28:02.640 --> 00:28:04.349
- is-is in the books. but...
<i>- Yeah.</i>

409
00:28:04.350 --> 00:28:06.768
My sister. you know.

410
00:28:06.769 --> 00:28:10.939
there've been a few...
characters that may or may not

411
00:28:10.940 --> 00:28:15.527
have been. you know.
loosely based on her. you know.

412
00:28:15.528 --> 00:28:17.028
the really rigid ones.

413
00:28:17.029 --> 00:28:19.739
<i>- That makes sense.</i>
- Oh. you've met her.

414
00:28:19.740 --> 00:28:20.865
<i>No comment.</i>

415
00:29:02.867 --> 00:29:04.660
Jinx Slater?

416
00:29:12.751 --> 00:29:14.794
Well. he was just here.

417
00:29:14.795 --> 00:29:16.546
Looks like he might've run in a hurry.

418
00:29:16.547 --> 00:29:18.798
Yeah. like...

419
00:29:18.799 --> 00:29:21.969
- killed my girlfriend and split?
- Could be.

420
00:29:24.054 --> 00:29:26.973
This kind of tat is something
that you eventually regret.

421
00:29:26.974 --> 00:29:30.226
- If you live long enough.
- Mm.

422
00:29:30.227 --> 00:29:31.644
See how he's looking at her?

423
00:29:31.645 --> 00:29:32.897
He loved her.

424
00:29:34.148 --> 00:29:36.025
Sure seems like it.

425
00:29:39.361 --> 00:29:43.072
So. what? Now. we think maybe
he didn't kill her because he loved her?

426
00:29:43.073 --> 00:29:46.409
Well. men kill women
they love all the time.

427
00:29:50.247 --> 00:29:52.332
- Huh.
- What you got?

428
00:29:52.333 --> 00:29:54.042
Fabric ink.

429
00:29:54.043 --> 00:29:56.253
The kind that disappears in water.

430
00:29:56.837 --> 00:30:01.049
You know. Chief Scarpetta was starting
to think that maybe Gwen was a spy.

431
00:30:01.050 --> 00:30:04.552
Being at Thor. Gwen would've had access
to a lot of secret shit.

432
00:30:04.553 --> 00:30:06.763
So...

433
00:30:06.764 --> 00:30:08.306
Think someone came for Jinx. too?

434
00:30:08.307 --> 00:30:11.142
Sure looks that way.

435
00:30:11.143 --> 00:30:13.728
You can't keep me here.
I know my rights.

436
00:30:21.111 --> 00:30:24.489
Jinx. this is a federal investigation.
and as such.

437
00:30:24.490 --> 00:30:27.867
we can keep you here as long as we want.

438
00:30:27.868 --> 00:30:29.827
Hell. we could even disappear you.

439
00:30:29.828 --> 00:30:32.121
We're the people who do that kind of shit.

440
00:30:32.122 --> 00:30:35.416
Do you know that a sickening proportion
of women in the United States

441
00:30:35.417 --> 00:30:37.877
are killed by their intimate partners?

442
00:30:37.878 --> 00:30:40.130
I didn't kill Gwen.

443
00:30:42.091 --> 00:30:43.091
I loved her.

444
00:30:43.092 --> 00:30:45.385
Loving her just makes us suspect you more.

445
00:30:45.386 --> 00:30:46.637
It wasn't me.

446
00:30:47.888 --> 00:30:49.305
I swear it wasn't.

447
00:30:49.306 --> 00:30:50.682
Mm-hmm.

448
00:30:50.683 --> 00:30:52.518
Who was it then?

449
00:30:55.563 --> 00:30:58.106
Please help yourselves.
We grow it all here.

450
00:30:58.107 --> 00:30:59.524
I'm good.

451
00:30:59.525 --> 00:31:02.360
Wait. so is it true you changed your name
to Yama Matthew?

452
00:31:02.361 --> 00:31:04.029
What is that? Is that a real thing?

453
00:31:05.239 --> 00:31:06.448
Thank you.

454
00:31:07.366 --> 00:31:10.451
In Buddhism. Yama means god of death.

455
00:31:10.452 --> 00:31:14.497
That's so funny. I-I always thought
the doc here was the god of death.

456
00:31:14.498 --> 00:31:17.750
No. I understand. the desire to have
some control over death. I really do.

457
00:31:17.751 --> 00:31:19.836
Once you've...

458
00:31:19.837 --> 00:31:21.671
once you've experienced it. you're...

459
00:31:21.672 --> 00:31:23.506
you're really never the same.

460
00:31:23.507 --> 00:31:25.008
I couldn't be the same

461
00:31:25.009 --> 00:31:27.051
- after what happened to my wife.
- No.

462
00:31:27.052 --> 00:31:29.387
The psyche. uh. it creates what I...

463
00:31:29.388 --> 00:31:31.889
I call workarounds. ways of coping.

464
00:31:31.890 --> 00:31:34.642
There are bad ways
and there are good ways.

465
00:31:34.643 --> 00:31:37.270
The good was to try to help
other people who'd lost people.

466
00:31:37.271 --> 00:31:39.523
Others who couldn't
find their way back to the living.

467
00:31:40.899 --> 00:31:42.609
That's what gave birth to this place.

468
00:31:42.610 --> 00:31:44.152
And what about the bad ways?

469
00:31:44.153 --> 00:31:46.321
- I'm sorry?
- You just said

470
00:31:46.322 --> 00:31:49.907
there were good ways and bad ways.
I'm curious about the bad ways.

471
00:31:49.908 --> 00:31:54.162
Do you know this. uh. this woman.
Gwen Hainey?

472
00:31:59.043 --> 00:32:00.335
No.

473
00:32:00.336 --> 00:32:03.338
- What about you? Have you ever...
- No. she does not.

474
00:32:03.339 --> 00:32:05.049
Can you let her speak?

475
00:32:07.301 --> 00:32:08.801
I don't know her.

476
00:32:08.802 --> 00:32:10.595
What does this woman
have to do with anything?

477
00:32:10.596 --> 00:32:12.347
She was murdered.

478
00:32:12.348 --> 00:32:15.768
And the weirdest part about that
is they found your prints in her condo.

479
00:32:21.482 --> 00:32:23.566
All right.

480
00:32:23.567 --> 00:32:27.279
I don't hold a grudge against either
of you for what you did to me. you know.

481
00:32:28.280 --> 00:32:30.448
- Us?
- We found your wife's killer.

482
00:32:30.449 --> 00:32:31.741
Yeah. that's what we did.

483
00:32:31.742 --> 00:32:32.950
Yes...

484
00:32:32.951 --> 00:32:36.621
but not before ruining my life.
my reputation.

485
00:32:36.622 --> 00:32:38.706
That was all in the pursuit of justice.

486
00:32:38.707 --> 00:32:42.378
And here you are again. pursuing justice.

487
00:32:43.379 --> 00:32:44.879
You need to go.

488
00:32:44.880 --> 00:32:47.799
Now. look. you-you're within your
rights to have us tossed. okay? But...

489
00:32:47.800 --> 00:32:51.678
until my curiosity's mollified
about what

490
00:32:51.679 --> 00:32:54.097
your prints are doing
inside a dead woman's condo.

491
00:32:54.098 --> 00:32:57.225
you're not gonna have much peace.
Yama Matthew.

492
00:32:57.226 --> 00:33:00.437
I haven't had any peace for 27 years.

493
00:33:01.438 --> 00:33:03.481
I get that. I understand.

494
00:33:03.482 --> 00:33:06.443
You're the medical examiner. yes?

495
00:33:07.778 --> 00:33:09.028
Mm-hmm.

496
00:33:09.029 --> 00:33:11.198
And you-you're retired?

497
00:33:11.782 --> 00:33:13.242
So...

498
00:33:14.326 --> 00:33:16.870
get the hell off my land.

499
00:33:26.714 --> 00:33:27.964
Thank you.

500
00:33:39.393 --> 00:33:42.145
She had marks on her wrists.

501
00:33:42.146 --> 00:33:45.064
You think she tried to off herself?

502
00:33:45.065 --> 00:33:47.316
I think someone tried to tie her up.

503
00:34:11.508 --> 00:34:12.759
Hi.

504
00:34:12.760 --> 00:34:15.136
I hope I'm not bothering you.

505
00:34:15.137 --> 00:34:17.346
May I come in a second?

506
00:34:17.347 --> 00:34:19.849
Yeah. Sure.

507
00:34:19.850 --> 00:34:21.769
Agent Wesley.

508
00:34:23.896 --> 00:34:26.355
- Um...
- Uh. can I get you anything?

509
00:34:26.356 --> 00:34:27.523
Oh. no. thanks. I mean...

510
00:34:27.524 --> 00:34:29.776
Maybe. I mean. if you're having something.

511
00:34:29.777 --> 00:34:31.361
Yeah. sure.

512
00:34:33.197 --> 00:34:36.491
Uh... Ugh...

513
00:34:36.492 --> 00:34:40.203
I just wanted to say. I had no idea
that you were being summoned today.

514
00:34:40.204 --> 00:34:44.332
Nor was I there
in-in any adversarial manner.

515
00:34:44.333 --> 00:34:46.292
I-I just...

516
00:34:46.293 --> 00:34:48.295
I wanted to assure you of that.

517
00:34:50.923 --> 00:34:52.466
Well. um...

518
00:34:53.967 --> 00:34:57.929
Maybe if you tell me
exactly what happened after I left.

519
00:34:57.930 --> 00:34:59.598
I-I might even believe you.

520
00:35:00.724 --> 00:35:03.017
- Lot of backpedaling.
- Mm.

521
00:35:03.018 --> 00:35:04.393
Right.

522
00:35:04.394 --> 00:35:07.940
You caught them off guard
knowing about the 911 call.

523
00:35:09.316 --> 00:35:13.778
That 911 call gets answered.
and Lori Petersen would still be alive.

524
00:35:13.779 --> 00:35:15.696
Amburgey and Boltz are elected officials.

525
00:35:15.697 --> 00:35:18.700
If that gets out. they're...
they're finished.

526
00:35:19.910 --> 00:35:22.286
Well. that's why he only gagged you
and he didn't...

527
00:35:22.287 --> 00:35:24.873
What. didn't fire me?

528
00:35:26.291 --> 00:35:27.500
You rattled them.

529
00:35:27.501 --> 00:35:29.628
Mm. yeah. if only.

530
00:35:32.089 --> 00:35:33.381
Anyway...

531
00:35:33.382 --> 00:35:36.217
I just wanted you to know
that I'm-I'm on your side.

532
00:35:36.218 --> 00:35:40.138
I wouldn't want to mess with you. at all.

533
00:35:58.949 --> 00:36:00.825
Aren't you supposed to do that
in your bedroom?

534
00:36:00.826 --> 00:36:02.243
Hey.

535
00:36:02.244 --> 00:36:05.121
- Lucy. um...
- Hi. I'm Lucy.

536
00:36:05.122 --> 00:36:06.998
- Are you Aunt Kay's boyfriend?
- Uh. uh.

537
00:36:06.999 --> 00:36:10.793
This is. uh. my niece. Lucy.
Lucy. this is. uh. Benton.

538
00:36:10.794 --> 00:36:12.503
Hello. Hello. Lucy.

539
00:36:12.504 --> 00:36:15.047
- Hello.
- Bed. Bed. now.

540
00:36:15.048 --> 00:36:18.009
It's not a big deal. Auntie Kay.
I see my mom kiss guys all the time.

541
00:36:18.010 --> 00:36:21.387
Oh. God. that's great.
that's really good. Um...

542
00:36:21.388 --> 00:36:22.763
That's my niece. She's 11.

543
00:36:22.764 --> 00:36:24.932
- I should go. She's 11?
- Yeah.

544
00:36:24.933 --> 00:36:27.810
I know. I know. Her mom is. um...

545
00:36:27.811 --> 00:36:29.395
Yeah. that doesn't matter.

546
00:36:29.396 --> 00:36:31.064
You should go.

547
00:36:44.995 --> 00:36:47.622
- Listen...
- Yeah. I'm gonna...

548
00:36:47.623 --> 00:36:49.875
- I'm gonna let you out.
- Yes. All right.

549
00:36:50.751 --> 00:36:53.420
Yeah. Yeah.

550
00:36:59.134 --> 00:37:00.302
Um...

551
00:37:06.016 --> 00:37:07.350
So...

552
00:37:12.356 --> 00:37:14.941
- What the hell?
- Was someone watching us?

553
00:37:28.872 --> 00:37:30.498
What's the latest?

554
00:37:30.499 --> 00:37:33.834
They used Palomar knots on Gwen Hainey.

555
00:37:33.835 --> 00:37:35.878
Strong. hard to tie.

556
00:37:35.879 --> 00:37:38.631
Favored by professional survivalists.

557
00:37:38.632 --> 00:37:41.635
Got to be pretty bored
to make survival a profession.

558
00:37:42.636 --> 00:37:45.930
And then the phone cords
that he used on Lori Petersen.

559
00:37:45.931 --> 00:37:47.390
Palomar knots.

560
00:37:47.391 --> 00:37:49.266
- Same ones?
- Yes.

561
00:37:49.267 --> 00:37:51.185
We got to get a warrant
on that fucking farm.

562
00:37:51.186 --> 00:37:54.438
Find out what kind of knots
that dumb fuck is tying these days.

563
00:37:54.439 --> 00:37:56.775
Well. he's not dumb. that's for sure.

564
00:38:00.946 --> 00:38:04.156
If you're right and it's been
Matt Petersen this whole time...

565
00:38:05.575 --> 00:38:06.826
Then we better fucking run.

566
00:38:06.827 --> 00:38:08.995
- Oh. we got to do more than run.
- And never look back.

567
00:38:08.996 --> 00:38:11.748
Yeah.

568
00:38:12.624 --> 00:38:14.250
Oh. it's Lucy.

569
00:38:14.251 --> 00:38:16.919
Uh. goddamn it. Jinx Slater in the wind.

570
00:38:18.714 --> 00:38:22.258
Blaise said to tell you
that they found invisible ink at his crib.

571
00:38:22.259 --> 00:38:25.678
Okay. What did I tell you? Spy.

572
00:38:25.679 --> 00:38:27.847
This proves my theory.

573
00:38:27.848 --> 00:38:29.724
- Uh...
- Where is Lucy?

574
00:38:29.725 --> 00:38:34.103
Well. Lucy is grabbing a bite
at Seven Seas with Blaise Fruge.

575
00:38:34.104 --> 00:38:35.563
She's with Blaise?

576
00:38:35.564 --> 00:38:37.773
Having dinner?

577
00:38:37.774 --> 00:38:41.110
Hey. you know that they're both from the
same... what do you call it? persuasion.

578
00:38:41.111 --> 00:38:42.737
- That's not what you call it.
- Oh. I think it is.

579
00:38:42.738 --> 00:38:43.904
Come on. you know that.

580
00:38:43.905 --> 00:38:45.781
All right.

581
00:38:45.782 --> 00:38:48.035
You're doing a good thing. though.

582
00:38:49.119 --> 00:38:50.995
For Lucy. really good.

583
00:38:50.996 --> 00:38:53.248
Surprisingly good. for you.

584
00:39:05.135 --> 00:39:09.306
<i>Just so you know.
I-I didn't want to have to show you this.</i>

585
00:39:11.808 --> 00:39:13.434
Please.

586
00:39:13.435 --> 00:39:15.603
I don't want to see that.

587
00:39:15.604 --> 00:39:16.729
Did you do this?

588
00:39:16.730 --> 00:39:19.899
He may look genteel.
but. I promise you. that's not the case.

589
00:39:19.900 --> 00:39:21.400
Agent Wesley has quite the reputation.

590
00:39:21.401 --> 00:39:22.735
Please stop.

591
00:39:22.736 --> 00:39:23.986
- Did you do this?
- Agent Wesley

592
00:39:23.987 --> 00:39:26.614
likes to talk to serial killers
just for kicks.

593
00:39:26.615 --> 00:39:28.532
I didn't fucking do it!

594
00:39:28.533 --> 00:39:30.327
Okay. Okay.

595
00:39:34.372 --> 00:39:37.958
Let's start talking about what Gwen
was really doing at Thor Labs

596
00:39:37.959 --> 00:39:39.460
and how you were helping her.

597
00:39:45.342 --> 00:39:46.717
<i>Okay. and then...</i>

598
00:39:46.718 --> 00:39:50.429
there's Dot goes to Paris

599
00:39:50.430 --> 00:39:53.642
and she gets lost at Euro Disney.

600
00:39:54.684 --> 00:39:56.560
They-they think she's. like...

601
00:39:56.561 --> 00:39:58.855
one of the Seven Dwarfs.

602
00:39:59.940 --> 00:40:02.274
<i>- Okay. yeah.</i>
- Yes. It's good. right?

603
00:40:02.275 --> 00:40:06.655
Then Dot makes a wish
on a shooting star...

604
00:40:07.656 --> 00:40:09.491
and gets a stepsister.

605
00:40:10.742 --> 00:40:12.285
No.

606
00:40:13.328 --> 00:40:14.787
<i>- No.</i>
- No.

607
00:40:14.788 --> 00:40:17.414
no. no.

608
00:40:17.415 --> 00:40:19.291
No. You are right.

609
00:40:19.292 --> 00:40:20.835
I think it's a stinker.

610
00:40:20.836 --> 00:40:24.046
I have been telling my publishers

611
00:40:24.047 --> 00:40:26.632
that that's a stinker from the beginning.

612
00:40:26.633 --> 00:40:29.176
but they just...
they keep wanting to publish it.

613
00:40:29.177 --> 00:40:30.804
I agree with you.

614
00:40:31.805 --> 00:40:36.768
Why didn't I know that you read my books
when you were. you know...

615
00:40:37.853 --> 00:40:38.853
Yeah.

616
00:40:38.854 --> 00:40:42.231
<i>Well. I guess we never really talked
that much before.</i>

617
00:40:42.232 --> 00:40:44.859
No. No.

618
00:40:44.860 --> 00:40:48.779
<i>There's something
I would like to say to you. Dorothy.</i>

619
00:40:48.780 --> 00:40:51.366
<i>And I really hope
that you take it the right way.</i>

620
00:40:52.450 --> 00:40:53.743
Okay.

621
00:40:56.830 --> 00:41:00.834
<i>Do you have to be so hard on Lucy
for spending time with me?</i>

622
00:41:03.295 --> 00:41:06.214
Well. I-I... I will admit it.

623
00:41:08.592 --> 00:41:10.135
I-I'm worried.

624
00:41:12.095 --> 00:41:15.640
I'm worried about her spending
this much time with you.

625
00:41:18.894 --> 00:41:21.061
I want her to have a real life.

626
00:41:21.062 --> 00:41:23.356
<i>But this is her real life.</i>

627
00:41:24.357 --> 00:41:25.942
Is it?

628
00:41:29.571 --> 00:41:31.448
Or is it her old life?

629
00:41:36.578 --> 00:41:38.246
Dorothy.

630
00:41:39.539 --> 00:41:40.957
I promise you...

631
00:41:41.958 --> 00:41:44.669
I promise from the bottom
of my heart...

632
00:41:45.670 --> 00:41:48.089
I would never do anything to hurt Lucy.

633
00:41:49.090 --> 00:41:50.550
Ever.

634
00:41:52.052 --> 00:41:53.720
She's my love.

635
00:42:01.436 --> 00:42:03.103
Wow.

636
00:42:03.104 --> 00:42:05.981
Wait. it's-it's so dark out.

637
00:42:07.692 --> 00:42:09.401
What-what time is it?

638
00:42:11.154 --> 00:42:12.738
It's so late.

639
00:42:12.739 --> 00:42:14.698
I-I didn't hear them come home.

640
00:42:14.699 --> 00:42:16.242
Did you hear them come home? I didn't.

641
00:42:16.243 --> 00:42:19.536
<i>Uh. I could try to locate them.
if you like.</i>

642
00:42:19.537 --> 00:42:20.746
No.

643
00:42:20.747 --> 00:42:23.290
Lucy probably just got dragged

644
00:42:23.291 --> 00:42:27.503
into my sister and Pete's.
you know. criminal nonsense.

645
00:42:27.504 --> 00:42:30.214
I've been deserted

646
00:42:30.215 --> 00:42:33.968
by them for the greener pastures
of death and murder.

647
00:42:35.804 --> 00:42:37.304
It's very lonely.

648
00:42:37.305 --> 00:42:40.475
being the odd man out of the group
all the time.

649
00:42:42.018 --> 00:42:43.811
You know?

650
00:42:43.812 --> 00:42:45.312
And...

651
00:42:45.313 --> 00:42:48.440
theoretically. that I...

652
00:42:48.441 --> 00:42:53.237
have more right to him
than her at this moment.

653
00:42:53.238 --> 00:42:55.572
You know. I just...
I don't know what's in it

654
00:42:55.573 --> 00:42:57.866
for my husband to be tethered

655
00:42:57.867 --> 00:43:00.745
to my weirdo sister once again.

656
00:43:01.746 --> 00:43:03.122
<i>Well. duh.</i>

657
00:43:03.123 --> 00:43:06.251
<i>I mean. Pete's always been in love
with Kay.</i>

658
00:43:27.397 --> 00:43:28.647
What?

